---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Legal — Aerial"
  description="License, attribution, and privacy disclosures for Aerial."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-24 pb-32 prose prose-invert">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-aerial-accent !mb-2 !mt-0">
      Legal
    </p>
    <h1 class="!mt-3 text-4xl md:text-5xl !font-bold tracking-tight text-aerial-text">
      License and attribution.
    </h1>

    <h2 class="text-aerial-text">Aerial license</h2>
    <p class="text-aerial-text-muted">
      Aerial is open-source software, released under the
      <a href="https://github.com/AerialScreensaver/Aerial/blob/main/LICENSE" class="text-aerial-link">
        MIT license
      </a>. © Guillaume Louel and contributors. The full license text is available in the source
      repository.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-aerial-text">Apple's videos</h2>
    <p class="text-aerial-text-muted">
      The macOS/tvOS aerial videos played by Aerial are produced by Apple and fetched directly from Apple's
      content-delivery network at first play, on each user's machine. Aerial does not host,
      mirror, or redistribute Apple's videos.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-aerial-text">Community expansions</h2>
    <p class="text-aerial-text-muted">
      Each community expansion ships with its own license, declared in its manifest. Installing
      an expansion is opt-in. The featured expansion from Joshua Michaels &amp; Hal Bergman is
      licensed under the terms at
      <a href="https://jetsoncreative.com/aeriallicense" class="text-aerial-link">
        jetsoncreative.com/aeriallicense
      </a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-aerial-text">Privacy</h2>
    <p class="text-aerial-text-muted">
      Aerial includes no telemetry, no analytics, no crash reporting of any kind. The app
      makes outbound HTTPS requests to: Apple's CDN (for videos), this site's
      <code class="text-aerial-text">appcast.xml</code> (for Sparkle update checks), and the
      expansions catalog when you open the Expansions browser. None of these requests carry user
      identifiers. Some optional features (Weather forecast via OpenWeather, Youtube streaming 
      via yt-dlp, etc) may individually track you in some limited form, we recommend you check 
      their respective privacy policies for more details. 
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-aerial-text">Trademarks</h2>
    <p class="text-aerial-text-muted">
      Apple, macOS, tvOS, Apple TV, and Mac are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S.
      and other countries. Aerial is a third-party project unaffiliated with Apple.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-aerial-text">Thanks</h2>
    <p class="text-aerial-text-muted">
      Aerial uses <a href="https://sparkle-project.org/" class="text-aerial-link">Sparkle</a> for
      auto-updates and
      <a href="https://github.com/sindresorhus/KeyboardShortcuts" class="text-aerial-link">
        KeyboardShortcuts
      </a>
      by Sindre Sorhus for the global hotkeys feature. The original project was started by John
      Coates in 2015 — see the
      <a href="https://github.com/JohnCoates/Aerial" class="text-aerial-link">historical repository</a>
      for the early commit history.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
